<p>
  Project Budget does not collect, transmit, store on a server, or share your financial data. There is no backend. The app runs entirely in your browser.
</p>

<h2>What is stored, and where</h2>
<p>
  Your profile data — accounts, categories, transactions, budgets, goals, and recurring templates — is written to your browser's <code>localStorage</code> under keys prefixed with <code>projectbudget:</code>. This data is local to the browser and device you are using.
</p>

<h2>What is transmitted</h2>
<p>
  Page assets (HTML, CSS, JS, fonts) are fetched from the Project Budget host and from <a href="https://fonts.bunny.net" rel="noopener">Bunny Fonts</a> (a GDPR-compliant font CDN that does not log IP addresses or set cookies). No request carries financial data.
</p>

<h2>Optional analytics</h2>
<p>
  If the maintainer chooses to enable site analytics, they will use <a href="https://umami.is" rel="noopener">Umami</a>, a privacy-respecting tool that does not use cookies and does not collect personal data. Analytics, if enabled, record page views only — never the contents of your budget.
</p>

<h2>Cookies</h2>
<p>
  Project Budget does not set cookies.
</p>

<h2>Exporting and clearing your data</h2>
<p>
  You can export your full profile to a JSON file at any time from the Export page. You can delete a profile from the Profiles page (a soft-delete that holds the data for seven days in case of an accident). To purge all Project Budget data, clear site data for this domain in your browser settings.
</p>
